    "description": "Smartwatches are great, but not all are stylish  and they're often packed with too many distractions for their own good. So what if you could graft the most essential smartwatch features onto a conventional wristwatch?  Thats the question Chronos hopes to answer with its tiny disc of the same name, and it's unlike any wearable I've used before. You just slap Chronos onto the back of your everyday watch and it gives you vibrating alerts and LED notifications any time you get a message. But how useful can a pseudo-smartwatch be when it doesn't have a display? Find out in MrMobile's hands-on tour of Chronos: the cure for the common wristwatch!   [SUBSCRIBE]     [ABOUT THIS VIDEO]  MrMobile's Chronos Hands-On was produced following two days with a Chronos watch accessory attached to an Eliot Havok Oxford Watch, both of which were loaned from Chronos. The Chronos accessory itself was paired with an iPhone 7 Plus.   [PRODUCTS IN THIS VIDEO]  Chronos:   Eliot Havok Oxford Watch:   Casio WSD-F10:   Pebble:   Apple Watch Series 2:      [MUSIC]  \"The Ballad of MrMobile.\" Mobile Nations, 2016  E-Business by Olive Musique, available at Premium Beat:    [SOCIALIZE]         [DISCLOSURE]  This post may contain affiliate links. See Mobile Nations' disclosure policy for more details:",
